    "2026-07-01 V18c-T — Pi version-bump static gate tests (paired V18c impl; pi-integration-contract version-bump-intro.md, version-bump-step2.md, version-bump-step2b.md, version-bump-steps-3-4.md, version-bump-triggers.md, provider-error-mapping.md, host-prerequisites.md #pic-34): adds src/extension/version-bump-gates.ts — the mechanical build-time gates of the contributor version-bump checklist, each a pure function over injected operands so both the conformant and drifted directions are testable and no gate reads an ambient primitive. Declares/inertly stubs (each returns no failures so its detection direction reds): surfaceInventoryPresenceFailures (step 2(a) positive surface-inventory presence), capabilityCountCoEditFailures (step 2(b) CAPABILITY_OBLIGATIONS.length===7 co-edit), enginesNodeEqualityFailures (step 3 three-way engines.node equality, operand (iii) the only live read), peerDependencyPinFailures (step 4 peerDependencies literal-read, PIC-34 widen-on-bump), reasonSnapshotConsistencyFailures (step 2(a) literal-array consistency on the SessionShutdownEvent['reason'] snapshot — runtime companion of the loom/typecheck/session-shutdown-reason-snapshot brand assertion), apiCoverageFailures + seedFieldFixtureFailures (step 6 provider seed-field Api-coverage + fixture), strictCapabilityProbeFailures (step 7 both arms: rename-detection + absence-under-the-probed-name, consuming probedName from SDK_SURFACE_INVENTORY). Adds real pinned data: SESSION_SHUTDOWN_REASON_SNAPSHOT ({quit,reload,new,resume,fork}, matching the pinned SDK) and PROVIDER_SEED_FIELD_TABLE. Extends V18a's SurfaceInventoryEntry with an optional per-kind payload and populates the four operand rows (pi-engines-node literal, peer-dep-range range, strict-capability-probe probedName, api-coverage apiUnionSnapshot). Plus tests/version-bump-gates.test.ts with 9 tests (peer-dep test cites PIC-34 inline; the rest name their version-bump step). Divergences (notes.md / decisions.jsonl): plan-side stale cross-reference for strict-capability-absence-pin resolved against the real anchors; per-row payload added to the shipped V18a inventory; gates are injected-operand seams with live reads deferred to V18c; PROVIDER_SEED_FIELD_TABLE duplicates the runtime binder's seed mapping. No new diagnostics-registry codes. Inert stub seam: no module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. Typecheck + lint clean; all 9 tests red on their own primary detection assertions because the V18c gate bodies are absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; V18a-T/V18b tests stay green. The 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change) are unaffected.",
    "2026-07-01 V18b — Inventory-closure audit gate (paired with V18b-T; pi-integration-contract audit shards — inventory-audit-intro.md §\"Inventory-closure audit\", audit-resolution.md, audit-recognised-shapes.md, audit-target-categories.md, audit-failures.md, audit-wire-and-canary.md). Fills runInventoryClosureAudit in src/extension/inventory-closure-audit.ts as a static-AST (ts.createSourceFile) walker over the in-memory file map: recognises category-(1) pi.<member> / category-(3) canonical-ctx member access (carrier = a function param named pi/ctx textually typed ExtensionAPI / ExtensionContext|ExtensionCommandContext), category-(2) named imports from the four @earendil-works/* peers + typebox, and the non-exemptible family-(4) shapes (import * as, default/dynamic/side-effect import, aliased import/export specifier, export *, off-canonical-name/annotation pi/ctx params); resolves each against SDK_SURFACE_INVENTORY (category-(1)/(3) rightmost-segment, category-(2) leftmost-segment), the typebox { Type }/{ Unsafe } sibling allow-lists, or a same-line // allow-pi-surface: marker (well-formed grammar per audit-resolution.md); surfaces every unresolved/prohibited reference as an audit/<class>/<family>/<symptom> record and emits exactly one audit/canary/scan-floor/* record (walked/recognised counters) per invocation. A marker on a family-(4) line routes to family-(5) (clause h) while the family-(4) shape record still fires (dual-emission). Adds formatAuditRecordLine (the four-tab-delimited discriminator/path:line/symbol/proposed-resolution wire form). Extends SDK_SURFACE_INVENTORY with three coined category entry kinds (pi-member/peer-named-import/ctx-member) and the entries the runtime touches (pi.on, pi.getCommands, ctx.waitForIdle, and 19 peer named-import rows). Land-green sweep (same commit, so the audit lands green on main not land-red): annotated the two real command-context handlers (factory.ts, minimal-loom.ts) ctx: ExtensionCommandContext, and renamed the nine non-Pi ctx/pi parameters breaching the canonical-carrier reservation (checkUnreachableCode ctx->unreachable; params.ts lowerTypeExpr + local ctx->lowerCtx; prompt-transport-mapping ctx->probeCtx; runtime-event-channel ctx->emitCtx x2; subagent-isolation ctx->extractionCtx; conversation-drive pi->eventApi). Adds tests/inventory-closure-audit-gate.test.ts — the npm test-side disk-walk driver + fail-closed wiring: walks the audited source tree (src/** minus *.test.ts/*.spec.ts/*.d.ts/__tests__//*.assert.ts under src/extension, symlinks opaque, case-sensitive .ts), emits the line-delimited wire stream on stdout, asserts zero violation records + exactly one green canary (walked/recognised > 0) over main, and reds against a seeded off-inventory pi.<member> access with the family-(1) record (Ships-when: green on main, red on seed). Divergences (notes.md / decisions.jsonl): static-AST scope approximation (function-ancestor carrier detection, not full binding resolution); stale-marker (s1/s2) and orphan/standalone malformed-marker detection deferred — markers are classified only on lines carrying a reference or family-(4) shape, so the audit self-tests green despite its own source discussing the marker string; family-(4) shape set limited to those the real tree exercises (destructured-param/subtype-creation/wrapped-annotation/captured-rebinding/computed-access/CJS shapes not yet detected); infra-failure handling minimal (only audit-internal throws). No new diagnostics-registry codes. No module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call in src/**. Typecheck + lint clean; the 10 V18b-T tests + the 2 gate tests green; full suite green apart from the 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change).",
    "2026-07-01 V18b-T — Inventory-closure audit gate tests (paired V18b impl; pi-integration-contract audit shards — inventory-audit-intro.md §\"Inventory-closure audit\", audit-resolution.md, audit-recognised-shapes.md, audit-target-categories.md, audit-failures.md, audit-wire-and-canary.md): adds src/extension/inventory-closure-audit.ts — the negative-direction surface-set-closure audit seam. Declares AuditClass (the three-class violation/infra/canary partition), AuditRecord (discriminator/path/line/symbol/proposedResolution — the per-family record shape + wire fields), AuditInput (an in-memory POSIX-path→UTF-8 file map + the SDK_SURFACE_INVENTORY rows + the typebox { Type } named-import and { Unsafe } member-access allow-lists), AuditResult (records + the two non-empty-scan canary counters walked/recognised), and stubs runInventoryClosureAudit inertly (empty records, both counters zero). Plus tests/inventory-closure-audit.test.ts with 10 tests keyed on the spec-pinned surfaces the leaf may not rename (the audit/<class>/<family>/<symptom> class segment, the per-family record-shape symbol values — family-(1) bare member, family-(4) shape literal, family-(5) the <n/a> sentinel — and the two canary counters; family/symptom tokens are implementation-owned): family-(1) an off-inventory pi.<member> fires exactly one violation-class record naming the member while an in-inventory pi.registerCommand access does not; a well-formed // allow-pi-surface: marker authorises an off-inventory surface (recognised, no violation) and the typebox { Type }/{ Unsafe } allow-lists resolve with no violation; a walk that recognises zero in-scope references trips a canary-class record (fail-closed) and every emitted discriminator stays under audit/ disjoint from the loom/typecheck/* prefix; the family-(4) shapes import * as pi, dynamic import(), aliased rebinding import { Foo as Bar }, and off-canonical-name / off-canonical-annotation ctx/pi parameters each fire a non-exemptible violation-class shape record (proposed-resolution never an allow-pi-surface marker), and an // allow-pi-surface: marker on a family-(4) line surfaces a family-(5) <n/a> marker record but does not suppress the family-(4) shape record (both fire on the same line, dual-emission). Divergence (notes.md / decisions.jsonl): the seam is a pure in-memory-file-map core (the disk walk + fail-closed infrastructure wrapper are owned by the paired V18b driver) and resolves against the inventory rows' id field (the V18a name for the spec's minimum-entry-shape path identifier). No new diagnostics-registry codes. Inert stub seam: no module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. Typecheck + lint clean; all 10 tests red on their own primary assertions (the expected violation / canary / family-(4) / family-(5) records are absent and the recognised counter is zero) because the V18b body is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason. The 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change) are unaffected.",
    "2026-07-01 V18a — SDK capability + surface inventory (paired with V18a-T; pi-integration-contract/inventory-audit-intro.md §\"SDK capability inventory\" PIC-15, capability-inventory-items.md items 1-7): fills the two pinned constants in src/extension/sdk-inventory.ts. CAPABILITY_OBLIGATIONS pins the seven named capabilities (items 1..7) with each row's factory-probed/verified-otherwise partition flag derived from the imported FACTORY_PROBABLE_CAPABILITIES set V9a exports via .includes(item) (not a literal [1,2,3,4,6] re-listed), so items 1/2/3/4/6 flag factory-probed and 5/7 verified-otherwise and the classification cannot drift from the Step-0 probe set. SDK_SURFACE_INVENTORY is the full Pi-side surface set - strictly broader than the seven capabilities: the nine factory-probable capability namespace-function members (pi.registerCommand/pi.sendUserMessage/createAgentSession/AgentSession.prototype.abort/pi.registerTool/pi.setActiveTools/pi.getActiveTools/pi.registerMessageRenderer/pi.sendMessage, Step 0 (c)), the two non-capability category-(1) pi.<member> namespace-function surfaces (pi.registerFlag/pi.getFlag), and the four non-namespace-function operand rows the V18c version-bump gates read (pi-engines-node->engines-pin, peer-dep-range, strict-capability-probe, api-coverage). No new diagnostics-registry codes. Constants stay Object.freeze'd (off the H2a mutable-binding scan); no broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. Both V18a-T tests green; typecheck + lint clean; full suite green apart from the 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change)."
